                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12439" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 27 Feb 2005 08:03:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, this unfortunately happens with MySQL Connector 2.x on JDK 1.4: Hibernate just checks the Connection interface before trying to call the prepareStatement version for auto-generated keys, even if the JDBC driver doesn&apos;t support this...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that MySQL Connector 3.x is GPL, so we can&apos;t easily ship it in the Spring distribution (2.x was LGPL). It&apos;s probably better to omit the MySQL driver completely in this case, and leave it up the user to download and add the driver.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12440" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 27 Feb 2005 08:07:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removed mysql-connector-java-2.0.14-bin.jar from Petclinic directory, and changed references in docs to MySQL Connector 3.x.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
